      "comment": "MOSCATO TIME (2) box seated before sticking on well to finish 6 lengths away in second (19.35) at this track in a Maiden over 340m. The form from her last run stacks up well. Capable of going well again. BLUE BLARNEY (5) has been in the minor money at both career runs, the latest finishing third (19.40) at this track. Safe beginner but tricky box to overcome. Overdue for a win and looks a leading chance here. SCOTT MATRIX (3) comes off an average effort last start when seventh at Richmond over 320m behind Midnight Kelly (19.14) in a Maiden. Was in the money the start prior. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Key runner on best form. CHERI POP (8) cannot be ruled out.",
